.SH NAME
HTMLInputElement.minLength \- HTMLInputElement: minLength property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]minLength\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLInputElement\f[R] interface indicates the minimum number of
characters (in UTF\-16 code units) required for the value of the
\f[CR]<input>\f[R] element to be valid.
It reflects the element\[cq]s \f[CR]minlength\f[R] attribute.
\f[CR]\-1\f[R] means there is no minimum length requirement.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] If the input has a value, and that value has fewer
characters than the \f[CR]minlength\f[R] attribute requires, the element
is considered invalid and the \f[CR]ValidityState\f[R] object\[cq]s
\f[CR]tooShort\f[R] property will be \f[CR]true\f[R].
.RE
.SH VALUE
A number representing the element\[cq]s \f[CR]minlength\f[R] if present
or \f[CR]\-1\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLE
Given the following HTML:
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]p\f[R]>
  <\f[B]label\f[R] for=\[dq]password\[dq]>Your password</\f[B]label\f[R]>
  <\f[B]input\f[R] id=\[dq]password\[dq] type=\[dq]password\[dq] minlength=\[dq]8\[dq] maxlength=\[dq]20\[dq] />
</\f[B]p\f[R]>
.EE
.PP
You can use the \f[CR]minLength\f[R] property to retrieve or set the
\f[CR]<input>\f[R]\[cq]s \f[CR]minlength\f[R] attribute value:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] inputElement = document.querySelector(\[dq]#password\[dq]);
console.log(\[ga]Element\[aq]s minLength: ${inputElement.minLength}\[ga]); \f[I]// \[dq]Element\[aq]s minlength: 8\[dq]\f[R]
inputElement.minLength = 12; \f[I]// updates the element\[aq]s minlength attribute value\f[R]
.EE
